    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 7A, B, C and D: Pre-embedding immunogold labelling followed by silver enhancement was used for the subcellular localization of CGRP immunoreactivity in axon terminals of mossy cells in the inner third of the molecular layer. The silver-enhanced gold particles were selectively associated with large dense-core vesicles (arrows) present in axon terminals that form asymmetrical synapses (open arrows) mostly with dendritic spines. Several dense-core vesicles without immunolabelling (small arrow in [A]) were also observed.\nNote on Antibody used: The paper uses rabbit anti-CGRP antiserum (1:10000; Baffy et al, 1992) followed by incubation with an antirabbit secondary antiserum conjugated to 1 nm gold particles (1:25, overnight, Amersham, Little Chalfont, England). The paper mentions that specificity of the Ab was tested, however, the literature is unavailable. The paper also describes the control experiments done to test for cross-reactivity of the antibody.. Experimental description: Adult (2-3 months old) male Wistar rats (Charles River, Budapest) were used.",
